# JavaScript guidelines

The canonical rule content lives in [`coding-rules/rules/javascript.md`](mdc:coding-rules/rules/javascript.md) — shared with Claude Code so the tools cannot drift.

When writing or editing JavaScript or TypeScript, read and follow `coding-rules/rules/javascript.md`: functional style with pure functions, composition over inheritance, async/await with handled promises, strict equality, destructuring, ES modules, and disciplined logging.
